            <h2 id="Home" class="fix-scroll">Home</h2>
            <h3>Who am I?</h3>
            <p>
                My name is Kaappo, I'm 18 years old and I currently I study at Otaniemi Upper Secondary School at their
                mathematics and science program. I have programmed since I was six, and thus programming is very close
                to my heart. Despite my relatively young age, I have a lot of experience developing software, both
                professionally and for fun.
            </p>
            <p>
                In addition to programming, my hobbies include photography, all event technology -related matters, and
                playing the guitar.
            </p>
            <h2 id="Portfolio">Portfolio</h2>
            <p>Here is a compilation of my personal projects that best represent my skills in various areas of
                information techology.</p>

            <ul class="no-bullets add-horizontal-rule">
                <li>
                    <h3 class="portfolio-header accent">Scientia</h3>
                    <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/KaappoRaivio/Scientia/master/src/assets/readme/concept1.png"  alt="Boat instruments in a grid"/>
                    <img class="portfolio-logo" src="public/res/favicon.svg" alt="" id="Scientia"/>

                    <p>Scientia (<code>/ˈsaɪənˌtɪa/</code>) is a boat instrumentation system which uses an open
                        standard, <a href="https://signalk.org/">Signal K</a> as its data source. It's capable of
                        displaying data from a <a href="https://github.com/SignalK/signalk-server">Signal K server</a>
                        in a clear and uncluttered way.</p>

                    <a class="read-more" href="portfolio/scientia"></a>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <h3 class="portfolio-header accent">WilmaInk</h3>
                    <img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/KaappoRaivio/wilmaInk/master/assets/1.png" alt="My school schedule on as it would be shown on an e-ink display" />
                    <img class="portfolio-logo" src="public/res/wilmaink.svg" alt="" id="WilmaInk"/>

                    <p>WilmaInk is a sister of my other project Wilmacrawler, which it uses as a back-end. WilmaInk
                        presents the data in a form that can be rendered on an e-ink display. This means limited resution, and very limited color palette, in my e-ink display's case 3 colors:
                        black, white, and red.</p>
                    <a class="read-more" href="portfolio/scientia"></a>

                </li>
            </ul>


